results.name: Smallest prime factor of 10^(2^n) + 1.
comment: 10^k+1 can only be prime if k is a power of 2. So far the only known primes of this form are a(0) = 11 and a(1) = 101. [Edited by _M. F. Hasler_, Aug 03 2019]
a(n)>=2^(n+1)+1; we have a(n) = 2^(n+1)+1 for n=7 and n=15.
link: Wilfrid Keller, Prime factors of generalized Fermat numbers Fm(10) and complete factoring status
xref: Essentially the same as A102050. - _Sean A. Irvine_, Feb 17 2013
results.author: _Sergio Pimentel_, Jan 22 2012
